Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.64,0:05:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Leema!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.23,0:06:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.13,0:06:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.64,0:06:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the distribution center.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.64,0:06:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they all messengers?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.98,0:06:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.67,0:06:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We collect items that people post across the fleet, and we hand them in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.20,0:06:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.67,0:06:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we get delivery jobs in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.23,0:06:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.69,0:06:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.03,0:06:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.32,0:06:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Melty! Saya!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.26,0:06:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.62,0:06:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How's the work?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.42,0:06:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotten the hang of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.57,0:06:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm learning bit by bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.92,0:06:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,With Amy as your mentor, \Nyou'll pick it up in a flash!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.76,0:06:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! I'll do my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.92,0:06:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up, girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.71,0:06:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got afternoon deliveries!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.18,0:06:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.57,0:06:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Good thing we can \Nsplit it three ways, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.39,0:07:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while since \Nwe all got the same area.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.73,0:07:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So then he asked me, "What present \Nwould a girl like you be happy with?"
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.19,0:07:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd love some new shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.33,0:07:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Mine are always wearing out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.66,0:07:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the point! \NDoes he have to ask {\i1}me{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.87,0:07:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a bit inconsiderate, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.58,0:07:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.79,0:07:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you just ignore him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.33,0:07:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy for you to say with \Na boyfriend waiting for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.54,0:07:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.62,0:07:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.57,0:07:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All done!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.68,0:07:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,See, if we split it up like this, \Nit makes things much easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.38,0:07:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.18,0:07:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.98,0:07:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.80,0:07:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not too familiar with \Nthe ships in this area yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.46,0:07:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.91,0:07:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,These ships are from the fleet I \Njoined with, so I know them well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.14,0:08:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.33,0:08:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is where I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.68,0:08:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Looks good to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.36,0:08:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Come over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.28,0:08:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.24,0:08:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! That's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.21,0:08:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is no place for amateurs!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.79,0:08:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.32,0:08:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Mayta!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.86,0:08:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Leema, you shouldn't bother them \Nwhen they're working.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.08,0:08:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.91,0:08:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.51,0:08:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you an engineer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.50,0:08:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.32,0:09:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So how do you manufacture this part?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.94,0:09:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the composition of the alloy? \NWhat torque of actuator do you use?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.73,0:09:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're that keen on machines, \Nyou should come and work with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.67,0:09:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We could use all the help we can get!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.44,0:09:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it right there, Pinion!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.70,0:09:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Mr. Pompadour!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.45,0:09:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Pompadour...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.07,0:09:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But for now, I'd like to \Nlearn more about Gargantia!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.99,0:09:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Ledo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.58,0:09:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.29,0:09:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job finding this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.60,0:09:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if we can pull it up again in one piece.{might need a devil fruit??}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.86,0:09:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been short on ships \Never since taking in Kugel's fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.14,0:10:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not exactly small.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.04,0:10:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would we put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.62,0:10:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We can harvest the Chrono's farms early.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.28,0:10:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That should do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.18,0:10:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.97,0:10:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This'll be fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.87,0:10:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.16,0:10:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.04,0:10:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.55,0:10:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go! I'm drenched in sweat!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.05,0:10:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, a bath after work is a gift from the heavens!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.88,0:10:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ledo. I heard they decided to \Npull up the sunken ship you found.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.69,0:11:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.78,0:11:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while since I last \Ngot to use my secret weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.11,0:11:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Secret weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.39,0:11:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! It's quite a show, \Nso look forward to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.48,0:11:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Leema showed me around the Kugel fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.37,0:11:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You're pretty organized for your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.07,0:11:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.69,0:11:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,"For your age," huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.91,0:11:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,She's only a year younger than you, Melty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.30,0:11:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's here, I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.37,0:11:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.79,0:11:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, Ledo was the real MVP today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.51,0:11:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.16,0:11:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't say anything about it to me, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.45,0:11:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you came together again? \NGlad to see you're getting along.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.90,0:11:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Gargantia sure has an impressive \Nassortment of facilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.14,0:12:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello! A marine mix for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.94,0:12:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.21,0:12:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.03,0:12:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, it's the ex-pirate queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.75,0:12:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn some respect!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.23,0:12:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's "pirate queen on vacation" to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.49,0:12:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She calls herself that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.35,0:12:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,My break's almost over, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.99,0:12:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing a big salvage op soon, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.87,0:12:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been tasked with securing \Nthe area so no one gets in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.13,0:12:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, we've been hired as bodyguards.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.43,0:12:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.39,0:12:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So you {\i1}do{\i0} work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.25,0:12:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.36,0:12:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You're Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.72,0:12:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.91,0:12:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Leema. Amy's showing me the ropes at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.77,0:12:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a messenger?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.33,0:12:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna hear your stories!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.31,0:12:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell me about the \Nflying Yunboro you rode in!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.52,0:13:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamber?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.52,0:13:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He was...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.72,0:13:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a machine built to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.23,0:13:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,He used gravity manipulation to fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.59,0:13:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He could understand any language,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.39,0:13:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and he used the immense power \Nat his disposal to protect his pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.54,0:13:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate battle armor,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.61,0:13:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a Machine Caliber.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.28,0:13:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.93,0:13:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He was Chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.83,0:13:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So he really was the same as \Nthe sky god's divine messenger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.08,0:13:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sky god?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.08,0:13:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean Colonel Kugel's Striker?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.44,0:13:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I'm from Lord Kugel's fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.68,0:13:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You are?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.57,0:13:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you tell me what happened to the Colonel and Striker?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.74,0:14:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Cutie spotted!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.40,0:14:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this? Do I see someone flirting?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.19,0:14:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Two-timing, even?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.14,0:14:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't say I blame you, Leema.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.49,0:14:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.32,0:14:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo, girls need constant attention, \Nor they start to worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.59,0:14:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep! And that goes for Amy too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.77,0:14:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember how she'd ask Chamber for advice in secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.92,0:14:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, uh, is there something Ledo would, \Nyou know, like to have?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.81,0:14:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamber?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.85,0:14:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The food and other supplies necessary \Nfor the Lieutenant's daily operation
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.52,0:14:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,are already provided to him on a steady basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.65,0:14:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I meant!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.90,0:14:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, like, something that'll \Nmake him happy or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.46,0:14:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, something that'll put a smile on his face!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.63,0:15:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It has already been ascertained that the Alliance's recreation program
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.38,0:15:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is ineffective on the Lieutenant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.91,0:15:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.78,0:15:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I get to know Ledo better?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.66,0:15:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,H-How do you know about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.48,0:15:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.88,0:15:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just advice, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.85,0:15:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind that stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.77,0:15:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.14,0:15:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.62,0:15:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A lovers' spat?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.69,0:15:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be nice to be young.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.13,0:15:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm almost jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.24,0:15:34.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.37,0:15:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo, I'm glad to see you're \Ndoing so well for yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.48,0:15:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but work's important too!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.59,0:15:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Salvaging's one thing, but have you \Ngotten a taste for engineering yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.17,0:15:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about, Pinion?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.29,0:15:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been teaching me a bit \Nabout how Yunboros work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.70,0:15:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you kidding me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.94,0:15:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I just felt sorry for him, taking orders from such a hardass all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.52,0:16:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Who're you calling a hardass?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.27,0:16:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.52,0:16:01.23,Alt,,0,0,0,,Leema.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.23,0:16:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.62,0:16:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always wondered how the \NColonel's fleet turned out the way it did.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.43,0:16:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.30,0:16:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,My home ship joined the fleet back when Lord Kugel and his messenger began guiding the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.00,0:16:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The fleet was united by the worship \Nof the sky god's emissary, Lord Kugel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.71,0:16:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But after the whalesquids were defeated
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.09,0:16:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and Priestesses Linaria and Aleria \Npassed away, everything changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.26,0:16:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We gave everything we had to sustain the fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.08,0:16:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Even dying was just seen \Nas another way to contribute.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.18,0:17:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,"To stay strong, dispose of the weak."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.40,0:17:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,"Convince those who can't fight
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.78,0:17:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that sacrificing themselves for the good of the group is the greatest joy."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.16,0:17:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the way of the \NGalactic Alliance of Humankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.68,0:17:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I find it hard to believe that the \NColonel would have wanted that, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.17,0:17:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.49,0:17:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,No one even knows exactly \Nwhen Lord Kugel lost his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.74,0:17:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If he'd still been alive, \NI'm certain we would have found a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.18,0:17:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I owed my life to him many times over.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.22,0:17:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't been able to find anything of the sort.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.46,0:17:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not easy to find out more about Chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.14,0:17:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.79,0:17:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I hoped we could find out more from the ejected cockpit that remained,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.78,0:18:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but the technology used is far beyond \Neven that of the ancients.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.31,0:18:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,These are all the scriptures my sister Linaria inherited from our father.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.76,0:18:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sorry that we couldn't be of help.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.12,0:18:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true at all. There is so much in these books that we of Gargantia did not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.26,0:18:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Humanity realized that their \Nplanet's days were numbered,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.76,0:18:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and most joined one of two rivaling factions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.89,0:18:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But some, few in number as they were, \Ndecided to look for another path.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.17,0:18:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We are the descendants of those people.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.63,0:18:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,All of humanity tried to survive in any way they could.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.70,0:18:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who left for the stars amidst that conflict must have felt the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.34,0:18:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They abandoned Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.33,0:18:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, I'd like to believe it was a \Ndifficult decision for them to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.78,0:19:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what happened to the people who left Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.40,0:19:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the only one here who does.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.09,0:19:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There has to be something I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.08,0:19:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.92,0:19:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been trying to find a way to \Ncommunicate with the whalesquids.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.14,0:19:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There might be a better way for \Nus to live, without conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.12,0:19:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'm just trying to make amends.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.60,0:19:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.46,0:19:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you feel responsible?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.12,0:20:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy, I live in fear every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.17,0:20:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.96,0:20:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The Alliance is still fighting an \Nall-out war with the Hideauze.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.34,0:20:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And deep inside, I actually feel like it's a necessary war.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.95,0:20:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But... You're here with us now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.90,0:20:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The galactic war you came from \Nis far, far away, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.11,0:20:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not relevant anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.68,0:20:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.43,0:20:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's very relevant. Everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.44,0:20:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything humanity does, \Nbe it here or there, is connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.89,0:20:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If we ever came into conflict with the whalesquids,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.18,0:20:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,or if the Hideauze found Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.69,0:20:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,would I be able to handle it \Ndifferently from the Alliance?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.01,0:20:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I find another way?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.75,0:20:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I couldn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.54,0:21:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What if I too had to throw away \Nsomething precious just to stay alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.04,0:21:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.30,0:21:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't come down to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.67,0:21:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd find a way. Just like back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.38,0:21:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You and Chamber did so much \Nto help us during that huge storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.85,0:21:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The huge storm...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.41,0:21:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Leema, you were listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.40,0:21:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't intend to—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.56,0:21:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, yes I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.85,0:21:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell me what happened with \NLedo and Chamber in that storm!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.07,0:22:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the boats got torn loose \Nand dashed against the hull!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.29,0:22:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Check for leaks!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.38,0:22:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The bulkheads are closed!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.04,0:22:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! But check anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.86,0:22:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the last one!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.66,0:22:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Over to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.97,0:22:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger! Moving along!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.65,0:22:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Secured!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.11,0:22:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Pull the crane!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.56,0:22:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Connection complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.77,0:22:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! Keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.60,0:22:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job, Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.50,0:23:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.86,0:23:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an emergency!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.08,0:23:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The Artemia's interlocks are damaged!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.52,0:23:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.55,0:23:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.68,0:23:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The support wires have all snapped,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.93,0:23:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and the interlock pylons are damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.54,0:23:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Only one is left.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.39,0:23:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.40,0:23:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The screw pods on both \Ngunwales are inoperable?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.06,0:23:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Commodore, more than five hundred \Npeople live aboard the Artemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.73,0:23:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They are in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.85,0:23:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Any bridges?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.25,0:23:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one left, but it could break any minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.05,0:23:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we repair the interlocks?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.14,0:23:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have the manpower.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.75,0:23:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediate repairs are out of question.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.32,0:24:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Urgent delivery!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.75,0:24:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a damage report!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.78,0:24:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Allowing such a large ship to drift freely \Nwould put the entire fleet at risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.02,0:24:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We will scuttle the Artemia.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.34,0:24:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The Artemia?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.87,0:24:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.79,0:24:34.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All personnel on the Artemia are to \Nevacuate immediately! Top priority!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.45,0:24:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Scuttle the Artemia!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.69,0:24:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Evacuate it right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.15,0:24:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Saya's ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.32,0:24:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.28,0:24:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.50,0:24:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.80,0:25:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Saya?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.33,0:25:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She isn't here!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.51,0:25:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,She's still on board!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.16,0:25:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a chance! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.08,0:25:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If she's to sink, I'm going down with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.08,0:25:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, stop being a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.16,0:25:21.08,Alt,,0,0,0,,I won't leave the ship I've lived my life on!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.85,0:25:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Take him with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.10,0:25:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.26,0:25:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.80,0:25:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,My sister will oversee the evacuation.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.69,0:25:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys leave too.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.36,0:25:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Fleiss!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.02,0:25:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't steer her anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.12,0:25:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point staying on the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.80,0:25:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, get going!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.82,0:25:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Bridge here!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.81,0:25:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.21,0:25:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The central tower's empty!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.22,0:25:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! I'm the only one on the bridge too.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.45,0:25:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry with the rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.35,0:25:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.80,0:25:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Saya!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.36,0:25:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.17,0:25:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.43,0:25:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard the ship's being scuttled, so I was worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.93,0:26:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just making sure no one's been left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.24,0:26:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll help. What areas are left?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.10,0:26:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The forecastle and the sterncastle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.01,0:26:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll check the forecastle, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.89,0:26:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.00,0:26:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true that we're abandoning the Artemia?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.10,0:26:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.06,0:26:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They're evacuating now!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.77,0:26:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they gonna be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.20,0:26:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Is anyone still here?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.11,0:26:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Evacuate now!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.24,0:26:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.31,0:26:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You go ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.27,0:26:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.73,0:26:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.83,0:26:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.22,0:26:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.06,0:26:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We're done!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.17,0:26:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Just us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.71,0:26:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.25,0:26:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's scuttle her and get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.90,0:26:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this really the only way?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.95,0:27:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Destroying the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.94,0:27:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She can't be steered anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.88,0:27:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And with only one interlock left, \Nshe could smash into the fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.11,0:27:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Better to sink her before it comes to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.08,0:27:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born and raised here.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.69,0:27:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never even heard of a storm this big.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.43,0:27:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There are some things in life \Nthat are simply beyond our control.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.26,0:27:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Artemia!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.34,0:27:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a huge wave coming! Get out of there right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.07,0:27:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Melty? I can't hear you properly!{idk it seemed pretty audible to me}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.23,0:27:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Say it again!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.97,0:27:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.66,0:27:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.87,0:28:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.61,0:28:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.36,0:28:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.52,0:28:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.72,0:28:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.11,0:28:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Detecting an abnormal angle \Nof inclination among the ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.46,0:28:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamber!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.28,0:28:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy! Saya!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.61,0:28:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.30,0:28:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.42,0:29:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.01,0:29:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We're close to capsizing!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.26,0:29:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Chamber! Maximum output!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.68,0:29:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.66,0:29:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, kiddo!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.07,0:29:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold her!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.41,0:29:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.77,0:29:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, reel it in!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.24,0:29:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.68,0:29:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good! Keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.15,0:29:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Look over there! We've got trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.53,0:29:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.54,0:29:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do now, Amy?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.38,0:30:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Emergency broadcast intercepted.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.22,0:30:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.75,0:30:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Artemia's broken loose!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.89,0:30:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Saya and Amy are still on board!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.48,0:30:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.51,0:30:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The vessel in question has lost \Npropulsion and steering ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.64,0:30:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It is most likely out of control.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.33,0:30:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's adrift?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.93,0:30:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Affirmative.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.86,0:30:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.20,0:30:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't move from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.19,0:30:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Straighten up, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.01,0:30:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a little more!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.01,0:30:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo, metalhead...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.27,0:30:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back inside and put these on!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.48,0:30:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.45,0:30:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Crap, we're drifting back!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.74,0:31:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hull recovering.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.68,0:31:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,She's back! She stopped listing!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.48,0:31:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Declination returning to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.70,0:31:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Balance is likely to be restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.34,0:31:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.88,0:32:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.42,0:32:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Threat level lowering.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.75,0:32:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.26,0:32:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I only managed thanks to Chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.72,0:32:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's gone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.46,0:32:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure even if something like that happened now,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.74,0:32:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.66,0:32:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You've always done everything you could.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.61,0:32:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.40,0:33:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right! Time to go down!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.55,0:33:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Bellows! The capture vehicle is lowering at a steady pace!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.65,0:33:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.71,0:33:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You all hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.03,0:33:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna raise a ship from her grave!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.86,0:33:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a treasure among treasures!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.96,0:33:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Lift her well!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.91,0:33:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.87,0:33:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Recheck the area!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.90,0:34:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Pinion! Letter for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.07,0:34:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.88,0:34:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You don't have any more deliveries?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.65,0:34:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I saved this one for last.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.28,0:34:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? You're worried about Ledo?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.54,0:34:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Uhh...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.21,0:34:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.08,0:34:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Pinion! The anchors!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.19,0:34:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.31,0:34:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you ready, guys?{PUT YA GUNS ON}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.45,0:34:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get this done!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.64,0:34:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Team one! Attach the guide wires to the hull!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.17,0:35:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Team two! Pull the main wires under the hull!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.95,0:35:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirm connection!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.91,0:35:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirmed!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.58,0:35:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to finish the job. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.41,0:35:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.35,0:35:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.32,0:35:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,My wire got stuck on something!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.79,0:35:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.87,0:35:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's collapsing!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.04,0:35:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out of there! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.92,0:36:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Go ahead! I've got this!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.30,0:36:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.90,0:36:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.84,0:36:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo went under!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.96,0:36:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.80,0:36:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Disconnect your cable!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.49,0:36:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.81,0:36:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.46,0:37:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How much air is left?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.75,0:37:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't good.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.44,0:37:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Open reserve tank.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.01,0:37:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Emergency injection of CO2 absorbent.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.70,0:37:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirm battery power.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.33,0:37:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Manipulator.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.47,0:37:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Comms.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.60,0:37:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.22,0:37:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me the communications cable...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.69,0:37:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone respond! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.28,0:37:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.60,0:38:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened down there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.01,0:38:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.43,0:38:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a sudden burst of gas,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.30,0:38:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the whole place collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.92,0:38:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Ledo?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.38,0:38:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he's alive, his air won't last long.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.16,0:38:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Then hurry up and dig him out!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.22,0:38:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's far too dangerous to go down there!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.82,0:38:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The rescue party would get buried too.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.19,0:38:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.68,0:38:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.36,0:38:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you do {\i1}something{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.94,0:38:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Bellows!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.58,0:38:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Bellows! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.06,0:38:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No response.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.70,0:39:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Second Lieutenant Ledo, \Npilot of Machine Caliber K6821! Anyone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.36,0:39:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No response.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.64,0:39:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It is likely that the Hideauze attack \Nleft them adrift with their reactor exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.41,0:39:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up and restore communications!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.57,0:39:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You useless piece of junk!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.88,0:39:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It is advised that you refrain from radio transmissions.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.68,0:39:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.90,0:39:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Multiple Hideauze life-signs detected.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.90,0:39:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They might notice this unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.08,0:39:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.94,0:39:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying I should just wait to be eaten?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.56,0:39:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Activate the emergency beacon!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.63,0:39:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't leave these decisions up to a machine!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.78,0:39:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.16,0:39:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As the pilot, you have final call on all decisions, \NSecond Lieutenant Ledo.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.42,0:39:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,If you choose to exercise that prerogative \Nand use your own judgment,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.60,0:39:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I will reevaluate the situation \Nand suggest the best possible course of action.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.83,0:40:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So your power depends on me, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.03,0:40:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.88,0:40:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I await your judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.48,0:40:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.94,0:40:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to die here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.53,0:40:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I are gonna survive, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.65,0:40:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.53,0:40:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I am an interface system that supports \Nand oversees the development of pilots.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.35,0:40:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I exist solely to set you up for success.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.56,0:40:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's right. Survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.91,0:40:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He told me I should trust myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.33,0:40:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And he told me he would trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.41,0:40:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't have much time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.99,0:40:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Think.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.73,0:40:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Think!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.85,0:41:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.13,0:41:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone who can dive, get in there!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.79,0:41:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Not enough air cylinders! \NScrape together all we've got!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.40,0:41:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.69,0:42:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Gather the ship captains.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.48,0:42:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask them to supply us \Nwith manpower and resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.18,0:42:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the medics on standby too.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.59,0:42:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.17,0:42:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.64,0:42:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go save him!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.83,0:42:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Leema?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.57,0:42:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can count on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.34,0:42:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.28,0:42:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming too!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.12,0:42:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.65,0:42:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to help!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.28,0:42:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.58,0:42:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You have other things you need to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.78,0:42:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,When these daredevils come back, we need you to greet them with a smile on your face!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.35,0:42:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make sure we get out alive. All of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.04,0:42:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.29,0:43:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.68,0:43:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind this!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.04,0:43:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They still haven't found him?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.18,0:43:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Rackage?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.67,0:43:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you useless fools even doing?{i'd put landlubbers, but...}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.65,0:43:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Make way!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.44,0:43:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Here I go!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.44,0:44:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to say, but no one is \Nallowed to die on my watch!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.96,0:44:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Rackage?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.96,0:44:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.70,0:44:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other side of this gap!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.33,0:44:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Amico!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.53,0:44:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Stronzo!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.98,0:44:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.54,0:44:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it up, Rackage!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.38,0:44:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.34,0:44:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He's alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.84,0:44:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.25,0:45:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,"I rerouted the compressed air \Nfrom the floaters into the cabin."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.31,0:45:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You're quite something, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.31,0:45:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen up, Ledo.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.33,0:45:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll force the gap open together.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.21,0:45:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The moment we do, \Ndetach the limbs and the floaters.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.89,0:45:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We only get one chance at this.{you only chance once}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.69,0:45:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.47,0:45:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.39,0:45:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll count down from three!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.46,0:45:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Three!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.65,0:45:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.86,0:45:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,One!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.07,0:45:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.80,0:45:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.22,0:45:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.97,0:46:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The machine's free!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.07,0:46:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo's all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.55,0:46:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hell yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.16,0:46:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.44,0:46:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness he's all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.81,0:46:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ledo...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.68,0:47:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.28,0:47:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad you're safe!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.60,0:47:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Amy...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.09,0:47:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.97,0:49:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Proceed to the next phase.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.54,0:49:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{space language}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.20,0:49:47.95,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}kore made wa betsu no michi ayundekita futari
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.20,0:49:47.95,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}We used to walk different paths
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.95,0:49:53.96,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}onaji jikan wo kizamihajimeta n da
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.95,0:49:53.96,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}Now our time together has begun
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.96,0:50:00.59,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}taisetsu na takaramono katachi wa mienai kedo
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.96,0:50:00.59,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}The truly important things are invisible to the eye
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.59,0:50:06.95,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}te wo tsunaidara fureta ki ga shita
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.59,0:50:06.95,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}I think I know what matters when I touch your hand
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.95,0:50:13.12,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}kimi no hitomi ni utsuru atarashii keshiki
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.95,0:50:13.12,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}I want to know what the future will be like
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.12,0:50:21.59,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}dare yori chikaku de watashi mo issho ni mitsumetai
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.12,0:50:21.59,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}I want to hear it directly from you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.59,0:50:27.86,ED+,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}oboeteite ne itsumo soba ni iru yo
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.59,0:50:27.86,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(150,150)\blur0.5}Remember, I'm right here
